Former Bafana Bafana goalkeeper and captain Senzo Meyiwa's tombstone has been vandalized, two months after it was unveiled. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - Former Bafana Bafana captain Senzo Meyiwa's tombstone has been vandalised. It was unveiled at the Chesterville Heroes Acre cemetery on 10 November. READ: Senzo Meyiwa murder case postponed to March 2021 Images of the destroyed tombstone were shared on the official Bafana Bafana Twitter account. Meyiwa was shot dead in October 2014 at Kelly Khumalo's home. At least five people are on trial for his murder. Police are still investigating who could have vandalised the tombstone. CORRECTION: Chesterville, Durban NOT Clermont. https://t.co/3YhT66cMkK